<paragraph base="SL32862" id="IAS39_AG98"><paranum>AG98</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 39"/><data name="paranum" value="AG98"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS39_P1158">A <xref base="SL134655" href="IAS39_9_hedge-accounting.dita#IAS39_9_hedge-accounting/IAS39_P0208" scope="local">firm commitment<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0131"/></ph></xref> to acquire a business in a business combination cannot be a <xref base="SL134658" href="IAS39_9_hedge-accounting.dita#IAS39_9_hedge-accounting/IAS39_P0211">hedged item<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0166"/></ph></xref>, except for <xref base="SL144810" href="../ifrs07/IFRS07_APPA.dita#IFRS07_APPA/IFRS07_P0864">foreign exchange risk<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0066"/></ph></xref>, because the other risks being hedged cannot be specifically identified and measured. These other risks are general business risks.</p></body></paragraph>